1
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:32,760
(Episode 23)

2
00:01:37,280 --> 00:01:38,240
Xiaomeng,

3
00:01:38,600 --> 00:01:39,880
is there anything for calling me

4
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:41,240
at this hour?

5
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:43,360
It's nothing.

6
00:01:43,880 --> 00:01:45,200
I just miss you.

7
00:01:47,040 --> 00:01:48,280
I see.

8
00:01:48,600 --> 00:01:50,440
How have you been?

9
00:01:51,520 --> 00:01:53,640
Don't worry, Uncle Fang.

10
00:01:53,920 --> 00:01:56,760
I'm good. My work's going well

11
00:01:56,800 --> 00:01:58,480
and I'm quite happy.

12
00:01:59,840 --> 00:02:04,120
But I need to check something with you.

13
00:02:05,280 --> 00:02:06,680
Sure, go ahead.

14
00:02:07,920 --> 00:02:11,080
Uncle Fang, were you present

15
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:12,920
when A Yan was born?

16
00:02:14,080 --> 00:02:15,000
Xiaomeng,

17
00:02:15,480 --> 00:02:17,120
why are you asking this?

18
00:02:18,560 --> 00:02:24,880
I wanted to celebrate
A Yan's birthday with him earlier

19
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:28,320
but he seemed reluctant.

20
00:02:28,760 --> 00:02:30,480
That's why I wanted to check with you.

21
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:33,320
Well, A Yan

22
00:02:33,360 --> 00:02:35,280
behaves differently

23
00:02:35,320 --> 00:02:36,600
from other kids since young.

24
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:38,960
He's born in Sydney.

25
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:41,120
At that time, Boss and I

26
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:44,280
were tied up in an acquisition project

27
00:02:44,600 --> 00:02:46,080
in China.

28
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:47,480
As you know,

29
00:02:47,680 --> 00:02:49,760
I had to stay with Boss.

30
00:02:50,240 --> 00:02:51,280
We had planned

31
00:02:51,320 --> 00:02:52,800
to go to Sydney

32
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:54,680
at the time of A Yan's birth.

33
00:02:54,920 --> 00:02:57,040
But right after we signed the contract,

34
00:02:57,080 --> 00:02:58,720
A Yan's mother told Boss

35
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:00,560
that she had given birth.

36
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:03,320
In other words,

37
00:03:03,480 --> 00:03:04,920
neither Uncle Zhou nor you

38
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:06,200
was present

39
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:07,240
when A Yan was born.

40
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:10,120
That's right.

41
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:11,760
A Yan was born

42
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:13,520
two weeks before the estimated due date.

43
00:03:13,880 --> 00:03:16,320
Boss and I couldn't make it

44
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:17,640
so A Yan's mother

45
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:19,480
had to stay in an overseas hospital

46
00:03:19,520 --> 00:03:20,920
all by herself.

47
00:03:21,080 --> 00:03:22,800
Even after many years later,

48
00:03:23,160 --> 00:03:25,280
Boss still felt guilty about it.

49
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:29,760
I see.

50
00:03:30,320 --> 00:03:31,240
Xiaomeng,

51
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:33,080
did you guys quarrel?

52
00:03:33,600 --> 00:03:35,280
Do think of a way to patch up.

53
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:36,800
No, we did not.

54
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:39,920
We're getting along fine.

55
00:03:41,040 --> 00:03:44,080
Uncle Fang, please send my regards

56
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:45,240
to Haixing and Sister Li.

57
00:03:45,280 --> 00:03:46,280
I miss you guys.

58
00:03:46,600 --> 00:03:47,760
I'll go visit you

59
00:03:47,920 --> 00:03:49,240
on the island sometime later.

60
00:03:49,560 --> 00:03:50,800
That's great.

61
00:03:57,560 --> 00:03:58,680
This child...

62
00:05:31,320 --> 00:05:32,240
Mom,...

63
00:05:32,960 --> 00:05:34,320
I've to go somewhere far.

64
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:36,920
Be well.

65
00:05:38,560 --> 00:05:40,000
Perhaps when I'm back,...

66
00:05:40,840 --> 00:05:42,680
no one will misunderstand you anymore.

67
00:06:00,880 --> 00:06:02,480
My most beloved dad is here.

68
00:06:05,520 --> 00:06:07,440
I've always disliked

69
00:06:07,480 --> 00:06:08,680
the offices on this floor.

70
00:06:09,280 --> 00:06:10,840
You can choose not to come.

71
00:06:11,080 --> 00:06:12,240
Shenghai is big.

72
00:06:12,280 --> 00:06:13,800
You can go anywhere you like.

73
00:06:13,840 --> 00:06:14,680
Look.

74
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:16,640
The buildings in front

75
00:06:16,680 --> 00:06:18,440
totally block the view

76
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:20,600
and I can't see the sunrise and sunset.

77
00:06:20,640 --> 00:06:21,720
I simply don't understand

78
00:06:21,760 --> 00:06:24,200
why Zhou Binli chose this floor

79
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:26,040
as the executive's office area.

80
00:06:28,280 --> 00:06:30,640
Dad, everyone has his own preference.

81
00:06:30,680 --> 00:06:32,840
Just like I hate coming to work here.

82
00:06:33,120 --> 00:06:34,360
You hate this?

83
00:06:34,720 --> 00:06:36,000
So what do you want?

84
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:38,000
It doesn't matter.

85
00:06:38,040 --> 00:06:39,920
At the end of the day,
I still have to listen to you.

86
00:06:40,760 --> 00:06:42,840
A Ze, you must understand that

87
00:06:43,240 --> 00:06:45,280
every choice we make

88
00:06:45,440 --> 00:06:47,560
needs to be thought over carefully.

89
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:50,080
Just like when you learnt fencing,

90
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:51,600
doing as you please

91
00:06:51,960 --> 00:06:54,040
would not win you any mark.

92
00:06:58,440 --> 00:06:59,520
Stop playing.

93
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:04,640
Listen.

94
00:07:05,480 --> 00:07:06,960
My project needs you.

95
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:08,760
What do you mean?

96
00:07:09,280 --> 00:07:10,480
What do I mean?

97
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:12,400
I want you to join me.

98
00:07:13,160 --> 00:07:14,520
No way, I've yet to

99
00:07:14,560 --> 00:07:15,840
complete my projects on hand.

100
00:07:15,880 --> 00:07:17,120
If I go over now,

101
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:19,520
everyone in Shenghai
would call me a good-for-nothing.

102
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:21,400
I'll get someone more suitable

103
00:07:21,440 --> 00:07:23,720
to take over your projects.

104
00:07:26,720 --> 00:07:27,760
A Ze,...

105
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:30,600
I've dumped all my cash

106
00:07:30,840 --> 00:07:33,640
into the Dikai Commercial City project.

107
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:35,880
Since you find this project promising,

108
00:07:36,080 --> 00:07:38,120
you're free to dump in
as much money as you like.

109
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:40,280
Listen to me.

110
00:07:40,720 --> 00:07:44,320
Zhou Yanzhao bid for
that piece of land at a very high price.

111
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:46,200
His capital chain...

112
00:07:47,320 --> 00:07:50,400
I'm sure he'll think of ways

113
00:07:50,640 --> 00:07:51,920
to hang on to this project.

114
00:07:53,120 --> 00:07:54,440
I'll give you three days

115
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:55,640
to consider.

116
00:07:56,080 --> 00:07:57,560
Familiarize yourself with Dikai.

117
00:07:57,960 --> 00:07:59,720
Think about it through

118
00:07:59,880 --> 00:08:00,840
a commercial angle.

119
00:08:02,640 --> 00:08:04,440
Fine, let's talk again three days later.

120
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:07,680
When I asked Zhou Yanzhao to consider,

121
00:08:07,720 --> 00:08:10,320
he gave me an answer within three seconds.

122
00:08:10,920 --> 00:08:12,400
At the Sports Institute
when we fought for championship,

123
00:08:12,440 --> 00:08:13,440
I was already not his match.

124
00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:15,680
Why do I still have
to compete with him now?

125
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:18,240
Give it some thought.

126
00:08:18,720 --> 00:08:21,760
I want you to win this time.

127
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:54,480
(Shenghai Hospital)

128
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:40,720
Xiaomeng, you're here.

129
00:09:41,880 --> 00:09:42,760
Director Lin.

130
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:44,280
You've not been here these few days.

131
00:09:44,320 --> 00:09:45,680
Tiankong misses you.

132
00:09:46,040 --> 00:09:47,520
I had something to attend to.

133
00:09:47,560 --> 00:09:48,440
I was away.

134
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:50,800
How's Tiankong recovering?

135
00:09:50,920 --> 00:09:52,200
He's recovering well.

136
00:09:52,440 --> 00:09:53,400
The doctor said

137
00:09:53,440 --> 00:09:55,360
he's getting better.

138
00:09:58,080 --> 00:09:58,880
Leave it here.

139
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:03,160
Director Lin,

140
00:10:03,640 --> 00:10:05,520
can I have a word with you?

141
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:06,640
Sure.

142
00:10:07,760 --> 00:10:08,800
Let's talk outside.

143
00:10:09,800 --> 00:10:10,640
Okay.

144
00:10:10,680 --> 00:10:11,680
Let's go out.

145
00:10:17,760 --> 00:10:18,560
Come on.

146
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:46,320
Xiaomeng, you said

147
00:10:46,360 --> 00:10:47,480
you've something to tell me.

148
00:10:47,840 --> 00:10:48,880
We can talk here.

149
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:04,360
Does this ring comes in a pair

150
00:11:04,480 --> 00:11:05,800
with the ring

151
00:11:06,280 --> 00:11:07,560
you gave Tiankong?

152
00:11:12,480 --> 00:11:13,520
You knew about it.

153
00:11:14,640 --> 00:11:16,120
You knew about it all along.

154
00:11:17,320 --> 00:11:19,480
That's why you deliberately
approached him.

155
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:22,040
No,

156
00:11:22,160 --> 00:11:23,200
I...

157
00:11:23,640 --> 00:11:25,080
I don't understand what you mean.

158
00:11:25,600 --> 00:11:27,720
You knew long ago who Zhou Yanzhao is.

159
00:11:28,680 --> 00:11:31,280
That's why you suggested Shenghai Group
helping the Children Welfare Center

160
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:33,720
to bring you and him closer.

161
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:36,040
You came back from overseas

162
00:11:36,480 --> 00:11:38,600
because of him, right?

163
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:47,960
I was away...

164
00:11:48,720 --> 00:11:50,000
because I went to Sydney.

165
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:53,560
I found a person in Sydney.

166
00:11:54,640 --> 00:11:56,520
He told me a story.

167
00:11:59,440 --> 00:12:02,520
Who is he? What did he tell you?

168
00:12:06,680 --> 00:12:07,960
He's a doctor.

169
00:12:09,600 --> 00:12:10,640
He told me...

170
00:12:12,160 --> 00:12:13,600
he once helped...

171
00:12:14,520 --> 00:12:15,720
to deliver the babies...

172
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:18,760
of two Chinese women
more than 20 years ago.

173
00:12:19,640 --> 00:12:21,280
He remembers the incident...

174
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,000
that day...

175
00:12:23,760 --> 00:12:25,160
very well because...

176
00:12:26,320 --> 00:12:28,200
that incident...

177
00:12:28,640 --> 00:12:30,160
made him lose his job...

178
00:12:31,400 --> 00:12:32,720
and ruined his future.

179
00:12:34,040 --> 00:12:35,680
I'm sure you're well aware

180
00:12:36,120 --> 00:12:37,960
of that incident too,...

181
00:12:38,760 --> 00:12:39,760
Director Lin.

182
00:12:53,280 --> 00:12:54,280
Why?

183
00:12:55,440 --> 00:12:57,520
Why were you so heartless?

184
00:12:57,800 --> 00:13:00,400
You abandoned your own child.

185
00:13:00,680 --> 00:13:01,600
I did not!

186
00:13:05,640 --> 00:13:06,680
I did not...

187
00:13:15,360 --> 00:13:18,480
I was very young then.

188
00:13:19,280 --> 00:13:20,760
I was still in college.

189
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:22,200
I was too young

190
00:13:22,240 --> 00:13:23,440
and I knew nothing.

191
00:13:24,040 --> 00:13:24,880
I was stupid

192
00:13:24,920 --> 00:13:26,280
and got pregnant.

193
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:30,200
I thought...

194
00:13:31,440 --> 00:13:33,080
it was real love...

195
00:13:34,160 --> 00:13:35,520
and we'd be together.

196
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:45,320
Later, the doctor said

197
00:13:46,040 --> 00:13:47,160
I was too weak

198
00:13:47,640 --> 00:13:49,000
to have an abortion.

199
00:13:50,720 --> 00:13:52,760
My family objected
to me giving birth to the baby.

200
00:13:52,800 --> 00:13:55,680
Even then,
I still gave birth to that baby.

201
00:13:56,240 --> 00:13:57,040
Doctor,...

202
00:13:58,000 --> 00:13:59,200
how is my niece?

203
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:02,760
Both the mother and baby are fine.

204
00:14:03,640 --> 00:14:06,280
They're just tired
and haven't woken up yet.

205
00:14:08,160 --> 00:14:09,400
Thank you.

206
00:14:16,880 --> 00:14:20,440
It's two weeks premature
but she still gave birth nonetheless.

207
00:14:21,720 --> 00:14:23,560
I already told you
to ask her to abort the baby

208
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:24,800
but you refused to listen.

209
00:14:25,240 --> 00:14:26,440
Keep your voice down.

210
00:14:28,760 --> 00:14:30,040
The baby's born but

211
00:14:30,240 --> 00:14:31,440
he doesn't have a father.

212
00:14:32,680 --> 00:14:33,520
Ling Ling's not married yet.

213
00:14:33,560 --> 00:14:34,800
With that child,

214
00:14:35,120 --> 00:14:36,880
her whole life will be ruined.

215
00:14:38,880 --> 00:14:41,000
No, she must not

216
00:14:41,320 --> 00:14:42,680
keep the baby.

217
00:14:44,640 --> 00:14:45,840
On the day

218
00:14:46,120 --> 00:14:47,240
I gave birth to the child,

219
00:14:47,560 --> 00:14:49,120
my uncle and aunt told me...

220
00:14:50,440 --> 00:14:51,920
he's dead.

221
00:14:55,960 --> 00:14:57,200
It can't be...

222
00:14:58,120 --> 00:14:59,200
It can't be...

223
00:15:00,280 --> 00:15:01,600
It can't be...

224
00:15:01,920 --> 00:15:03,880
-My baby's not dead!
-Yueling...

225
00:15:03,920 --> 00:15:05,960
-Aunt, you must be lying.
-Yueling...

226
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:07,560
-Yueling.
-You must be lying.

227
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:08,680
Yueling,

228
00:15:09,080 --> 00:15:11,920
it's all fated, Yueling...

229
00:15:12,480 --> 00:15:14,000
How can this be?

230
00:15:14,440 --> 00:15:18,000
How can this be? My baby...

231
00:15:23,040 --> 00:15:25,360
My baby...

232
00:15:27,080 --> 00:15:29,760
My baby...

233
00:15:30,560 --> 00:15:32,720
She told me he's dead.

234
00:15:35,240 --> 00:15:37,720
Xiaomeng, I had

235
00:15:37,760 --> 00:15:39,600
no other choice at that time.

236
00:15:40,360 --> 00:15:42,840
I could only believe her.

237
00:15:45,760 --> 00:15:46,560
And you...

238
00:15:47,560 --> 00:15:48,400
found out later

239
00:15:48,440 --> 00:15:49,880
that the child's still alive?

240
00:15:52,280 --> 00:15:53,200
Yes.

241
00:15:55,160 --> 00:15:56,560
Aunt suffered from cancer...

242
00:15:57,520 --> 00:15:58,720
and told me this secret

243
00:15:59,200 --> 00:16:00,760
before she passed on.

244
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:07,120
I've to tell you a secret.

245
00:16:09,480 --> 00:16:13,800
You child is still alive.

246
00:16:17,160 --> 00:16:19,560
Aunt... Aunt, what did you say?

247
00:16:20,720 --> 00:16:22,000
My child is still alive?

248
00:16:22,360 --> 00:16:24,560
Where is he then? Where is he?

249
00:16:25,400 --> 00:16:28,800
We gave him to a woman...

250
00:16:29,360 --> 00:16:32,680
by the name of Fang Meijiao.

251
00:16:33,240 --> 00:16:34,640
Baby, sleep well.

252
00:16:38,480 --> 00:16:40,520
Miss, please give me the baby.

253
00:16:44,280 --> 00:16:46,360
It's already been 12 hours since he died.

254
00:16:46,400 --> 00:16:47,760
We must take him away.

255
00:16:47,960 --> 00:16:50,000
No, he's not!

256
00:16:50,400 --> 00:16:51,680
He's my baby.

257
00:16:52,320 --> 00:16:55,320
-Miss, it's okay.
-My baby just falls asleep.

258
00:16:56,840 --> 00:16:58,120
Come, help me please.

259
00:16:58,440 --> 00:16:59,240
Please...

260
00:16:59,400 --> 00:17:01,000
don't take my baby away.

261
00:17:01,240 --> 00:17:02,920
-Please...
-We'll take care of him.

262
00:17:03,320 --> 00:17:05,280
I can't live without him.

263
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:06,600
Please...

264
00:17:06,840 --> 00:17:09,320
-It's okay.
-don't take my baby away.

265
00:17:10,160 --> 00:17:10,960
Please...

266
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:12,760
don't take my baby away.

267
00:17:17,120 --> 00:17:18,240
Please...

268
00:17:18,480 --> 00:17:20,600
don't take my baby away.

269
00:17:22,240 --> 00:17:24,120
Please...

270
00:17:25,240 --> 00:17:26,480
Please...

271
00:17:26,520 --> 00:17:28,880
don't take my baby away.

272
00:17:29,760 --> 00:17:30,840
Miss,...

273
00:17:31,480 --> 00:17:32,800
I can save your baby.

274
00:17:34,160 --> 00:17:35,280
What did you say?

275
00:17:39,760 --> 00:17:40,640
You should...

276
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:43,120
calm down first.

277
00:17:43,920 --> 00:17:45,080
If you wish,

278
00:17:45,440 --> 00:17:48,120
your baby can be alive again.

279
00:17:50,840 --> 00:17:51,880
Really?

280
00:18:11,800 --> 00:18:14,800
Your child is well.

281
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:18,680
Your uncle and I did you wrong.

282
00:18:20,360 --> 00:18:23,640
But we did it for your good.

283
00:18:24,400 --> 00:18:27,120
Please don't blame us.

284
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:42,680
After I found out my child's alive,...

285
00:18:43,520 --> 00:18:46,080
I looked for him everywhere.

286
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:48,080
I finally found him.

287
00:18:50,120 --> 00:18:51,440
He's with the Zhou Family.

288
00:18:54,320 --> 00:18:55,840
His name is A Yan.

289
00:18:57,160 --> 00:18:59,240
He was already this tall.

290
00:19:00,800 --> 00:19:02,080
